                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="61400" author="linda" created="Wed, 26 Jun 2013 17:59:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch has landed. Marking this ticket fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59976" author="linda" created="Tue, 4 Jun 2013 16:48:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated Section 26.2 &quot;Reporting a Lustre Bug&quot;. Patch is ready for review at:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,6545,patchset=1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,6545,patchset=1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53650" author="jamesanunez" created="Sat, 9 Mar 2013 17:08:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The current documentation for this section points to &lt;a href=&quot;http://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/tools/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://downloads.whamcloud.com/public/tools/&lt;/a&gt; for a Lustre diagnostic tool, but there is no diagnostic tool there. &lt;br/&gt;
In the short term, we should point to &lt;a href=&quot;http://downloads.lustre.org/public/tools/lustre-diagnostics/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://downloads.lustre.org/public/tools/lustre-diagnostics/&lt;/a&gt; where the tool actually exists or remove this section from the manual.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe this is a separate ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26980" author="cliffw" created="Thu, 19 Jan 2012 17:02:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve created a wiki page, here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/~cliffw/How+to+file+a+good+bug+report&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/~cliffw/How+to+file+a+good+bug+report&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
However, lustre-diagnostics-1.6-wc1 still point the user towards bugzilla.lustre.org, so I am reluctant to include any content on this tool until that bit is resolved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="25949" author="cliffw" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 18:29:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will create a wiki page. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23570" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2011 13:57:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An additional note for this ticket is that the content generated should probably appear on our public wiki.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, either a wiki page could be written and copied to the Manual - or vice versa.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the former is preferred, I can do the manual conversion.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20614" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 3 Oct 2011 09:41:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Location of the relevant section in the manual:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual-reviews/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.html#dbdoclet.50438198_30989&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-manual-reviews/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/lustre_manual.html#dbdoclet.50438198_30989&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20590" author="rhenwood" created="Sun, 2 Oct 2011 12:51:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Waiting on bug reporting procedure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
